{
  "texts": [
    "Problem StatementService robots operating in shared spaces (e.g., homes, hospitals, offices) face critical safety challenges when interpreting natural language commands in dynamic environments.",
    "These challenges manifest in three key scenarios:• Misunderstanding Natural Language Commands:Ambiguous instructions (e.g., \"Get me a drink\") lack details like object type, location, or delivery destination.",
    "Such ambiguity risks unsafe actions, such as fetching a hot beverage without specifying handling constraints.",
    "• Conflict Between Commands and EnvironmentalConstraints: User instructions may conflict with realworld conditions.",
    "For example, a hospital robot ordered to deliver medication might encounter blocked paths or improperly stored items, requiring immediate plan adjustment to avoid harm."
  ]
}